# zDash Canonical Agent Roster

Use this roster for current and future zDash implementation phases.

Compatibility rule:
- Keep backend/API `agent_id` values stable for routing, tests, URLs, and event correlation.
- Use the new human display names in dashboards, docs, reports, and agent metadata.
- Treat legacy names as aliases only.

## Canonical roster

### Legendary

| Stable agent_id | Display name | Title | Legacy alias |
|---|---|---|---|
| `ceo` | Alexander Prime | CEO - Visionary Leader | CEO |

### Epic

| Stable agent_id | Display name | Title | Legacy alias |
|---|---|---|---|
| `janie` | Sophia Lane | Coordinator - Manager | Janie |
| `guardian` | Victor Hale | Risk Manager | Guardian |
| `editor` | Elena Voss | Content Specialist | Editor |
| `social` | Maya Quinn | Social Media Specialist | Social |
| `graphic` | Julian Reed | Design Specialist | Graphic |
| `trading` / strategy modules | Damien Cross | Trading Specialist | Trading Specialist |

### Rare

| Stable agent_id | Display name | Title | Legacy alias |
|---|---|---|---|
| `joe` | Nathan Cole | Analyst - Developer | Joe |
| `friday` | Isla Grant | Scheduler - Automation | Friday |

## Recommended wording

Use:

```text
Alexander Prime delegates execution to Sophia Lane. Sophia Lane coordinates Victor Hale, Isla Grant, Nathan Cole, Elena Voss, Julian Reed, Maya Quinn, and Damien Cross.
```

Avoid new user-facing copy that says:

```text
CEO -> Janie -> Guardian / Friday / Joe / Editor / Graphic / Social
```

unless the context is explicitly about legacy compatibility.

## Phase prompt rule

When updating `docs/prompts/phase*.prompt`, keep class/module names if they are code identifiers, but update user-facing text:

- `CEO agent` -> `Alexander Prime agent (stable id: ceo)`
- `Janie agent` -> `Sophia Lane agent (stable id: janie)`
- `Guardian agent` -> `Victor Hale agent (stable id: guardian)`
- `Friday agent` -> `Isla Grant agent (stable id: friday)`
- `Joe agent` -> `Nathan Cole agent (stable id: joe)`
- `Editor Agent` -> `Elena Voss agent (stable id: editor)`
- `Graphic Agent` -> `Julian Reed agent (stable id: graphic)`
- `Social Agent` -> `Maya Quinn agent (stable id: social)`
- `Trading Specialist` -> `Damien Cross agent / strategy specialist`

## Safety note

Renaming agents must not change safety gates or defaults. Trading, automation, and publishing paths remain dry-run, mock, read-only, or approval-gated unless explicitly enabled by guarded configuration.
